text:
Sorry for the wall of text. I can never catch your streams due to work, but I figured I'd throw my thoughts out there.
1:43:25 - Well. About that nurse, she'll get less happy the more people move in. If you just make a neo-brutalist apartment bloc (glory to Arstotzka), none of your tenants will be terribly thrilled. You COULD theoretically give her a little shack with the basics way the heck out in the boonies, or bury her in a hole in the ground with a table, a chair, and a candle.
1:45:00 - The Minishark seems a bit chintzy or underwhelming by the numbers, until you consider that it dishes out STOOPID amounts of dakka, and that EVERY. SINGLE. HIT. causes 6 damage, PLUS!!! the seven damage from the musket balls. When the entirety of space and time is filled -- indeed, comprised -- of nothing but dakka, then you will be dishing out such damage that you'll basically sandpaper enemies completely out of existence.
2:03:13 - Blessed event. It's always cool to see a star come down and just absolutely cream a monster.

Love the NPC hovel Gura

Ironically enough you inspired me to start playing terraria again, only for the first couple worlds generated to be auto named "The Shantytown of Disgust" and "The Lousy Settlement" so it's now my ultimate goal to make the absolute worst npc housing possible for both worlds. by comparison to what I'm doing you're a professional architect. though I do end up with a lot of fairly unique Death hovels scattered all over the world, by the end of a playthough about half the surface world becomes lava and rope bridges due to their sheer presence.
